  origin = "HEXA-SKIN.tape was a lattice-tautology stub generated by the hexa-bio mass-split 153b5a2 — ~96 'EXACT' rows claiming engineering and biology numbers (sensor density σ²=144/cm², 8 sensor modalities = σ-τ, skin temperature 33 °C = σ·n/φ-n/φ, skin pH 5.5 = sopfr+μ/φ, 10⁸ MEMS cycles = (σ-φ)^(σ-τ), etc.) were derived FROM the n=6 invariant lattice. The footer self-certified '96개 EXACT 파라미터 모두 n=6 공식에서 유도 (100%)' — exactly the lattice-fit-as-derivation anti-pattern hexa-bio AGENTS.tape g1/g2/f1/f3 and LATTICE_POLICY explicitly forbid."
  user-decision = "2026-05-16: rewrite HEXA-SKIN.tape from scratch as the electronic-skin / stretchable bioelectronics SSOT (wearable conformal sensors + epidermal electronics + intrinsically stretchable conductors + wearable biosensing), mirroring the HEXA-WEAVE.tape precedent (6d9eb32) and the florea ANDROGENETIC-ALOPECIA.tape gold standard. Skin DISEASE biology stays in florea (referenced, not shadowed — f3)."
  authored = "Hand-written with real stretchable-electronics + wearable-biosensor science. §1 platform (Rogers epidermal-electronics + Someya large-area route). §2 mechanics (serpentine geometry isolation, intrinsically stretchable conductors, cracked-metal Lacour/Wagner, conformal contact mechanics including bending stiffness ∝ t³, ionic skin / hydrogel transparent conductors). §3 sensor modalities (pressure piezoresistive/capacitive/piezoelectric/triboelectric; strain; temperature; biopotential dry electrodes; sweat-analyte multiplex à la Gao 2016; self-healing à la Tee/Bao 2012; multimodal integration). §4 power/wireless (harvesting routes; NFC battery-less; BLE; OECT biosignal recording; Bao 2022 intrinsically stretchable display; magnetoreception class). §5 SEVEN real-limit anchors (biocompat / long-term wear; power-harvesting ceiling; wireless-bandwidth + adhesion durability joint frontier; motion + sweat + water artifact; rigid-island / soft-skin mechanical mismatch; dry-electrode SNR floor; sweat-to-blood correlation; in-silico → wet-lab epistemic boundary)."
  citations = "10 real @X :: literature entries: Kim DH et al 2011 Science 333:838-843 (epidermal electronics, Rogers — exact volume/page asserted); Tee/Bao 2012 Nat Nanotechnol 7:825-832 (self-healing — exact volume/page asserted); Gao et al 2016 Nature 529:509-514 (wearable sweat sensor, Javey — exact volume/page asserted); Someya et al 2004 PNAS 101:9966-9970 (large-area flexible pressure-sensor matrix — exact volume/page asserted); Rogers/Someya/Huang 2010 Science 327:1603-1607 (materials & mechanics review — exact volume/page asserted); Sekitani & Someya 2010 Adv Mater (primary-authors/era, exact volume not asserted); Lacour/Wagner et al 2003 Appl Phys Lett (primary-authors/era, exact volume not asserted); Bao 2022 Nature intrinsically stretchable AMOLED (primary-authors/era, exact volume/page not asserted); Sun/Suo 2012 Nature tough hydrogel / ionic skin (primary-authors/era, exact volume not asserted). Author/era-only flag explicitly carried on each uncertain entry."
  n6-stance = "Declined as a derivation tool. @F f_lattice_fit (id=f_lattice_fit, pattern containing 'lattice-fit') + @N n6_honest_stance state plainly: electronic-skin engineering has no derivational n=6 invariant. Bending stiffness scales as t³ (continuum mechanics, not σ/τ/φ). Stretchability comes from fracture mechanics + serpentine/buckled geometry + intrinsically stretchable composites. Skin biology numbers (33 °C, pH 5.5, ~100 µm epidermis, ~140/cm² Meissner-fingertip) are anatomy/physiology numbers from the cited literature — any numerical coincidence with σ²=144 or sopfr+μ/φ=5.5 is COINCIDENCE ONLY, never derivation. The 96-EXACT 'n=6 공식에서 유도 (100%)' footer self-certification is explicitly falsified by this rewrite."
  governance = "Complies with hexa-bio AGENTS.tape g1/g2/g3/g5_sister_repo_cli/g8_in_silico_only/f1/f2/f3 + LATTICE_POLICY. Scope set to 'in-silico bioelectronic-substrate simulator consistency SSOT · NOT clinical / regulatory claim' per g8. Sibling axes / sibling repos (florea for skin disease) referenced via @X, never shadowed — f3."
  preserved = "Top primer (grammar reference cold-read by any LLM/agent/human) + sibling-log banner + @V :: spec [active] version='1.2' all retained. Identity @I id001 keeps id (hexa-skin), parent (dancinlab/hexa-bio), sibling-log (HEXA-SKIN.log.tape) — kind/brief/scope/rewritten-from rewritten."
  deleted = "All 96 lattice-tautology @D 'row_*' EXACT-parameter rows + the ASCII section banners (now empty after stub removal) + the lattice-fit Testable-Predictions stubs + the lattice-derived Mk.I–V evolution table + the lattice-fit Cross-DSE rows + the lattice-fit checklist + the lattice-fit dependency rows. Replaced wholesale with §0 identity / §1 platform / §2 mechanics / §3 sensors / §4 power-wireless-recent / §5 real-limits / §6 honest n=6 stance / §7 testable predictions / §8 cross-links / §9 literature citations — mirroring HEXA-WEAVE.tape precedent."
  lint = "python3 selftest/tape_lattice_honesty_lint.py HEXA-SKIN.tape --json → __TAPE_LATTICE_HONESTY__ PASS (has_guard=true, has_stance=true, grounded=true; zero deriv_hits / deriv_warnings since the new tape contains no live lattice-derivation lines and the @F guard / @N stance bodies are recognised by the linter)."
